{
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The Panama Canal operates within fixed borders, yet its hydrological system is continuously reconfigured through technical and legal adjustments to its watershed."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "In 2024, the Panama Canal Authority (ACP) announced an adjustment to the Canal watershed boundaries, expanding the spatial framework through which water is managed, monitored and allocated. This redefinition actively reorganized territory by incorporating new rural basins (and its populations) into Canal's operational domain."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "The expansion of watershed limits reproduces territorial effects in advance of material infrastructure. With new boundaries the Canal deploys new technical studies, environmental assessments, and planning processes that render projects such as the proposed Río Indio reservoir adminsitratively viable and strategically necessary. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "uuid": "66c8f866-efaf-45bd-9d0f-d3f3fe898fea",
      "includes": [
        "media",
        "annotations",
        "label",
        "description"
      ],
      "start": 1344,
      "end": 1353,
      "file": "8a77badf-7a01-466f-ad7e-443f308a3dbf",
      "type": "event",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "However, this is not the first time the Canal watershed has been redefined. When the administration of the waterway was transfered from US to Panamanian control in 1999, Law 44 was passed, formalizing a restructured watershed, extending its limits to incorporate rural territories into the Canal’s hydrological system. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "National debates about the Panama Canal expansion shed light on how this expansion will require the construction of new infrastructure: new dams and reservoirs in rural areas. Campesino protest movement emerged in response and, in 2006, president Martin Torrijos revoked Law 44."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "Timeline:",
          "bold": true
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": ""
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "1997 — Severe drought lowers Canal reservoir levels"
        }
      ],
      "align": "left"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "1999 — Law 44 expands the Canal watershed (Río Indio included within the new limits)"
        }
      ],
      "align": "left"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "1999-2006 — Campesino protests "
        }
      ],
      "align": "left"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2006 — Law 44 revoked"
        }
      ],
      "align": "left"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2007 — Documentary Familia released"
        }
      ],
      "align": "left"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "align": "left",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2016 — Panama Canal expansion completed (without new dams or reservoirs)"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2020s — Intensifying debates over water scarcity and Canal sustainability"
        }
      ],
      "align": "left"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2024 — Adjustment to the Panama Canal watershed boundaries (Río Indio is included)"
        }
      ],
      "align": "left"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "children": [
        {
          "text": "2026 — Río Indio reservoir project reactivated as national water strategy\n"
        }
      ],
      "align": "left"
    },
